article.headline: Alabama A&M 70, South Dakota State 66
article.story: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Andrew Williams scored 19 points and hit a clinching 3-pointer and Evan Hilton's jumper with 1:39 left put Alabama A&M ahead to stay in a 70-66 victory over South Dakota State on Saturday in a consolation game of the BCA Classic at Ohio State's Value City Arena. The Bulldogs (1-1), who had led most of the game, fell behind 66-65 on Andy Kleinjan's 3-pointer with 2:19 left. After Hilton hit his big shot, the Jackrabbits (0-2) missed two shots. Andrews then made a 3-pointer with 24 seconds left. Both teams lost their season openers on Friday in the tournament. Alabama A&M advances to meet Princeton on Sunday and South Dakota State will play VMI. Hilton and Trant Simpson each added 11 points for A&M, which won despite shooting 37 percent from the field. Mickell Gladness had 13 rebounds and Hilton had 10. The Bulldogs hit 18-of-25 free throws to just 4-of-12 by the Jackrabbits. Kleinjan led South Dakota State with 21 points, with Cadwell scoring 13 and Kai Williams 12. Blake Yackley had 12 rebounds.
